ps://www.vlaio.be/nl/media/179\">annex to the Ministerial Decree of 26 February 2016</a> (a <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/economie-en-ondernemen/een-eigen-zaak-starten/nace-code\">NACEBEL code</a> indicates the main activity the company performs). Sometimes companies have multiple activities and therefore have multiple NACEBEL codes. The main activity of the enterprise is then the activity that generates the most turnover.</li><li>the company is in order with everything according to the regulations in the Flemish Region, e.g. no arrears in social security debts.</li><li>the project must be primarily aimed at improving the current or future functioning of the company. People who want to undergo training because they want to change the direction of their business can receive support for this training through the SME portfolio if the NACE code of the current activity of their business allows it.</li></ul><p>Double subsidy is not allowed. If a business has received an intervention from another subsidy system, it cannot be cumulated with the SME portfolio. Only an intervention in the trainee's salary may be combined with the SME portfolio (e.g. Flemish training leave).</p>","nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"<p>Alleen kmo's, eenmanszaken, vrije beroepen (zoals artsen, advocaten, accountants, ...), zelfstandigen en zelfstandigen in bijberoep kunnen gebruikmaken van de kmo-portefeuille voor <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/economie-en-ondernemen/opleiding-en-advies/overzicht-van-projecten-die-in-aanmerking-komen-om-betaald-te-worden-met-de-kmo-portefeuille\">opleiding of advies</a> als</p><ul><li>ze samenwerken met een <a href=\"https://op.vlaanderen.be/op/bezoeker/initZoekCriteria.do\">geregistreerde dienstverlener</a></li><li>de exploitatiezetel (elke vestiging of activiteitencentrum met een bepaalde stabiliteit) van de onderneming in het Vlaamse Gewest gelegen is.</li><li>ze tot de privésector behoren (met een aandeel van de overheid kleiner dan 25%).</li><l