"<h3><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/economie-en-ondernemen/opleiding-en-advies/aanmelden-en-de-rechten-tot-de-kmo-portefeuille-beheren\">Register and manage rights to the SME portfolio</a></h3><p>Surf to the SME <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/kmo-portefeuille\">portfolio website</a>, click on the pink 'Apply' button and apply as an entrepreneur (not as a natural person). After registering, you will be taken to the Entrepreneurs' Desk. At the bottom right, you can start an application by clicking on the green button.</p><p>If you want to use the SME portfolio for the first time, you need to make sure you have the rights for your company to do so.</p><ul><li>Are you known as a legal representative in the Crossroads Bank for Enterprises (CBE) and want to manage the applications in the SME portfolio yourself? Then there is no problem and you can apply immediately in the SME portfolio.</li><li>Are you known as a legal representative in the CBE but will not manage the applications in the SME portfolio yourself? Then you can <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/economie-en-ondernemen/opleiding-en-advies/aanmelden-en-de-rechten-tot-de-kmo-portefeuille-beheren\">give</a> an <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/economie-en-ondernemen/opleiding-en-advies/aanmelden-en-de-rechten-tot-de-kmo-portefeuille-beheren\">employee the right</a> to manage applications in the SME portfolio.</li><li>Are you an employee and want to manage applications? Then you must ask the main access manager of the company or the legal representative after he has designated himself as main access manager in the Access Management System (BTB)) to give you the right to manage <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/economie-en-ondernemen/opleiding-en-advies/aanmelden-en-de-rechten-tot-de-kmo-portefeuille-beheren\">applications in the</a> SME portfolio.</li></ul><p>A company that is registered in the CBE but whose status is 'not yet active' cannot yet apply for support. If the status is on active, you can submit an application, even for training that started before the company was on active if the 14-day deadline has been respected.</p><h3><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/economie-en-ondernemen/opleiding-en-advies/projectaanvraag-indienen-in-de-kmo-portefeuille\">Applying for subsidies</a></h3><ul><li>For a grant application, follow this procedure:<ul><li>You can only apply when your company's status in the CBE is set to 'active'.</li><li>First, enter into an agreement or registration with a registered service provider for training or consultancy.</li><li>Submit your grant application online. This can be done up to 14 calendar days after the performance start date (e.g. training starts on 1 March, application must be made by 15 March). You do not need to notify the service provider of the application, he will be notified via e-mail.</li><li>The application is automatically confirmed. The service provider no longer has to approve, he continues to monitor that the aid application meets the conditions of the SME portfolio, if not he can still refuse the aid application.</li><li>After the application, you will immediately receive the details to deposit your own share of the costs in your electronic SME portfolio (Sodexo). You have 30 calendar days to do so.</li><li>Once your deposit is received, the Flemish government will deposit the subsidy in your portfolio.</li><li>Now you can pay the service provider with your electronic SME wallet. It can take up to 14 calendar days for the payment to be made. For foreign service providers, this may take longer.</li></ul></li></ul><p>You can stop a project application if you have submitted an incorrect application or if the service has been cancelled.</p>"},"@type":"Procedure","order":0}],"websites":[{"naam":{"nl":"Kmo-portefeuille (VLAIO.be)","en-x-generated":"SME portfolio (VLAIO.be)","nl-BE-x-formal":"Kmo-portefeuille (VLAIO.be)","nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"Kmo-portefeuille (VLAIO.be)"},"url":"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/kmo-portefeuille","@type":"Website","order":0},{"naam":{"en":"Subsidies for entrepreneurs"},"url":"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/andere-doelgroepen/flanders-innovation-entrepreneurship/subsidies-entrepreneurs/subsidies","@type":"Website","order":1}],"financieleVoordelen":[{"beschrijving":{"nl":"<p>Hoeveel <strong>steun</strong> u krijgt, is afhankelijk van de grootte van uw onderneming. De steun is beperkt tot een bepaald maximumbedrag dat u jaarlijks kunt opnemen. U kunt vrij kiezen of u dat bedrag inzet voor advies of opleiding of voor een combinatie van beide. De kosten die in aanmerking komen voor subsidie via de kmo-portefeuille zijn <strong>altijd exclusief btw</strong>. De btw betaalt u rechtstreeks aan de dienstverlener.</p><ul><li>Kleine ondernemingen krijgen 30% steun binnen het jaarlijks steunplafond van 7.500 euro.</li><li>Middelgrote ondernemingen krijgen 20% steun binnen het jaarlijks steunplafond van 7.500 euro.</li></ul><div data-table><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td>Opleiding of advies</td></tr><tr><td>Kleine ondernemingen</td><td>steunpercentage 30%, steunplafond 7.500 euro (sinds 1 januari 2020)</td></tr><tr><td>Middelgrote ondernemingen</td><td>steunpercentage 20%, steunplafond 7.500 euro (sinds 1 januari 2020)</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>De <strong>aanvaardbare kostprijs</strong> van een opleiding bedraagt minimum 100 euro, exclusief btw. De aanvaardbare kostprijs van een advies bedraagt minimum 500 euro, exclusief btw. Verplaatsingskosten van de opleidingsverstrekker en cateringkosten zijn aanvaardbaar als kost voor zover ze in een functionele relatie staan met de opleiding (cateringkosten beperkt tot 25 euro/per dag per persoon). Kosten voor cursusmateriaal komen in aanmerking wanneer het cursusmateriaal uitsluitend wordt gebruikt tijdens de opleiding.</p><p>Er wordt jaarlijks een globaal subsidiebudget voorzien. Wanneer het voorziene budget is toegekend, kunt u geen steunaanvraag meer